From 787f251b3e8a53dd46eaf46adabcdb17f839530d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 07:31:25 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Refactor monolithic sweep script into modular HPC search
 framework

Reorganize the single-file parametric sweep + MCMC orchestrator into a
modular package while preserving the search/sampling mathematics verbatim
(verified bit-identical: grid/coupled enumeration, stretch-move proposals,
initial ensembles, Gelman-Rubin and autocorrelation diagnostics):

- config/: YAML-driven configuration (SLURM directives, parameter bounds,
  static variables, MCMC priors) with a Python hooks module for callables
- src/scanner/: legacy line/grid search wrapped in an extensible Scanner
  base class (GridScanner, CoupledScanner)
- src/optimizer/: MCMC sampler (migrated stretch-move ensemble) plus a new
  gradient-free Nelder-Mead solver; both drive the submit-wait-parse loop
- src/slurm/: sbatch dispatcher with central job registry, plus a new
  watchdog daemon detecting missing outputs, NaN logs and stalled files,
  with status.csv logging, scancel and parameter-scaled resubmission;
  deployable as an independent sbatch agent
- src/analysis/: ResultParser (DataFrame/CSV/SQLite) and plotting suite
  (1D sensitivity, 2D heatmaps, MCMC corner/trace/convergence) saved to
  results/plots/
- main.py: centralized CLI (--mode scan|optimize|watch|analyze)
- README.md, MANUAL.md, requirements.txt, environment.yml

Co-Authored-By: Claude Fable 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
